WEBVTT

00:02.080 --> 00:05.360
<i>Now the story of a wealthy family
who lost everything...</i>

00:05.440 --> 00:07.360
<i>and the one son
who had no choice...</i>

00:07.480 --> 00:09.400
<i>but to keep them all together.</i>

00:14.680 --> 00:16.280
<i>It's Arrested Development.</i>

00:18.400 --> 00:21.680
<i>Before going to work,
Michael decided to have a little fun.</i>

00:21.760 --> 00:25.440
I'm doing a little cost-projection
analysis for a mini-mall.

00:25.560 --> 00:27.960
Wow. That's pretty cool you
know how to do all that stuff.

00:28.040 --> 00:33.120
Yeah. Well, maybe your old man is just a
little bit cooler than you thought he was.

00:33.240 --> 00:37.600
Stupid. Stupid chair.
Very stupid chair.

00:37.720 --> 00:41.240
But it's also this stupid
model home furniture.

00:41.320 --> 00:44.520
Maybe I oughta get myself one of those
nice leather chairs from work.

00:44.640 --> 00:48.520
- People can take chairs home from work?
- Well, not everybody.

00:48.640 --> 00:51.000
But I'm the president of
the Bluth Company since Dad's in jail.

00:51.080 --> 00:53.760
It's okay if I take a little
something from work, you know?

00:53.880 --> 00:57.240
Yeah, but isn't that why Grandpa's in jail,
because he took things from work?

00:57.320 --> 00:59.200
You're a good kid, you know that?

00:59.320 --> 01:03.280
I mean, a chair costs money,
so it's like stealing, and you always say...

01:03.400 --> 01:05.040
Not stealing. Not.

01:05.120 --> 01:09.520
I'm the one that taught you
stealing is bad, all right?

01:09.600 --> 01:12.800
I'm just saying, you know,
if I got a leather chair, okay?

01:12.880 --> 01:15.360
And I get to lean back...
Oh, this one's gonna go.

01:17.600 --> 01:22.560
Leather chair? So, you're against stealing,
but skinning cows is cool with you.

01:22.680 --> 01:27.200
I'm fine, by the way. Frankly, your concern
is getting embarrassing.

01:27.320 --> 01:30.160
- Since when are you against leather?
- You're not even a vegetarian.

01:30.280 --> 01:32.520
<i>I'm not against the insides.
People need meat to survive.</i>

01:32.640 --> 01:35.000
You are aware they don't remove it
from the cow surgically, right?

01:35.080 --> 01:39.040
Hi, Michael.

01:39.160 --> 01:42.640
Marta, hi. Hey, it's Marta.

01:42.760 --> 01:46.160
Hey, Marta, everybody.
Great to see you.

01:46.240 --> 01:49.200
- I was just looking for Gob.
- Well, you're his girlfriend.

01:49.280 --> 01:51.480
<i>Michael wished Marta
was his girlfriend.</i>

01:51.560 --> 01:53.760
<i>A secret he had only shared
with Lindsay.</i>

01:53.880 --> 01:56.960
Actually, we had a big fight.
He thought I was belittling his career...

01:57.040 --> 02:00.440
- but I never would do that.
- Neither would I. What career?

02:00.520 --> 02:03.520
- The magic?
- Oh, the tricks. The little tricks.

02:03.640 --> 02:04.535
- Those are great.

02:04.536 --> 02:07.120
- Well, he didn't like my
reaction to his new one.

02:07.200 --> 02:09.120
Real needle. Real apple.

02:10.759 --> 02:13.080
Real neck.

02:15.480 --> 02:19.200
