04:33.360 --> 04:35.200
Let me be clearer.

04:35.280 --> 04:39.200
Tell him Rollo wants him to
say good-bye to his legs.

04:52.360 --> 04:54.840
<i>- Michael went looking for Gob.
- Mom.</i>

04:54.920 --> 04:58.400
I'm so glad you're here. I want you to help
me break up your brother and his girlfriend.

04:58.520 --> 05:01.120
Well, I'm all for that.
We've just gotta find him first.

05:01.240 --> 05:04.280
- He's locked on the balcony.
- Oh.

05:04.360 --> 05:06.720
You meant Buster.
I thought you were talking about Gob.

05:06.840 --> 05:09.560
No. I will not have Buster
dating my best friend.

05:09.640 --> 05:12.480
<i>Tension had been high
between the two Lucilles...</i>

05:12.600 --> 05:14.960
<i>since Buster had announced
he'd been dating her.</i>

05:15.040 --> 05:17.029
<i>Although neither had addressed this,</i>

05:17.030 --> 05:19.680
<i>both had given indications
of their true feelings.</i>

05:19.800 --> 05:21.148
- Mom, you're ruining our fort.

05:21.149 --> 05:23.280
- I mean, she's been a
family friend for years.

05:23.360 --> 05:25.880
It's just... creepy.

05:25.960 --> 05:29.240
Hi, buddy. Mom, I think
you might be overreacting.

05:29.320 --> 05:31.520
She changed him as a baby.

05:31.600 --> 05:34.920
Okay. That-That's about
the creepiest thing I've ever heard.

05:35.040 --> 05:37.080
That's why she didn't look surprised.

05:37.160 --> 05:40.760
You're the only child who chose a spouse
I liked, and she's the one who had to die.

05:40.840 --> 05:43.640
I know. That's rough for you.
Mom, I'm looking for Gob.

05:43.720 --> 05:47.120
There's some people after him, and I
don't know whether it's gambling or what...

05:47.200 --> 05:50.200
but, um, they wanna break his legs.

05:50.280 --> 05:52.600
It's a good thing he's already got
that little scooter.

05:52.680 --> 05:56.320
Oh, don't give me that look.

05:56.440 --> 05:58.760
I happen to be
a more caring mother than most.

05:58.880 --> 06:01.760
- Where's my bed?
- I put it in storage.

06:01.880 --> 06:05.480
I guess you'll just have to decide which
Lucille you want to spend your nights with.

06:05.600 --> 06:11.000
Okay. Before I leave this place
for the last time ever, has anyone seen Gob?

06:11.080 --> 06:15.080
I saw him last night
at the Playtime Pizza Theater. On my date.

06:15.200 --> 06:17.640
Of which I have
another one tonight.

06:17.760 --> 06:20.000
And I'm going to
continue dating, Mom.

06:20.120 --> 06:22.800
Sounds a little bit like "dating Mom. "

06:22.880 --> 06:26.360
- It's starting to feel a little like it.
- Hmm.

06:26.480 --> 06:29.960
<i>Lucille decided she needed
the help of Buster's father.</i>

06:30.080 --> 06:32.720
<i>Unfortunately,
after a recent escape attempt...</i>

06:32.800 --> 06:35.800
<i>George Sr. had been
put in solitary confinement.</i>

07:01.960 --> 07:04.440
<i>Michael went to find
his brother at his latest gig.</i>

07:04.520 --> 07:06.760
- What's up, Mike?
- Yeah. What are you doing here?

07:06.880 --> 07:09.560
Can't get any work, Mike.
Magicians' Alliance has blackballed me...

07:09.640 --> 07:11.480
- from every venue in town.
- Hmm.

07:11.560 --> 07:13.560
Even my own so-called girlfriend
doesn't believe in me.

07:13.640 --> 07:16.160
Well, I don't wanna get into
that part of your life anymore.

07:16.280 --> 07:19.120
Okay. Listen, I just came here to tell you
that this guy named Rollo...

07:19.200 --> 07:21.080
pulled me over
and made some threats.

07:21.160 --> 07:23.520
- What kind of threats?
- He said to say good-bye to your legs.

07:23.640 --> 07:26.520
I don't know whether
this guy's a mobster, a loan shark...

07:26.600 --> 07:28.480
- something equally scary.
- A magician.

07:28.600 --> 07:32.680
I think you're confusing scary with silly.
This guy was frightening. He was in a limo.

07:32.800 --> 07:36.520
No, he's a magician.
He replaced me in the Alliance.

07:36.640 --> 07:38.760
<i>He's the reason I gotta
do my act in this hellhole.</i>

07:38.880 --> 07:41.240
- Why does he wanna break your legs?
- He doesn't wanna break my legs.

07:41.320 --> 07:43.640
- He wants to take my legs.
- I-I don't...

07:43.720 --> 07:47.040
The legs... The bottom half of
my saw-the-lady-in-half trick.

07:47.160 --> 07:49.240
No, not now. I'm showing him
how to do the trick.

07:49.320 --> 07:52.320
<i>Two chicks curl up in a box.
We call one the head and one the legs.</i>

07:52.440 --> 07:53.666
- So that's how they do it.

07:53.667 --> 07:55.800
- God, I gotta stop
giving these things away.

07:55.880 --> 07:57.600
The top half there,
what do you do about that?

07:57.680 --> 08:00.200
- I just get a volunteer from the crowd.
- Oh, yeah?

08:00.320 --> 08:02.840
The old top half quit when she found out
I was sleeping with the legs.

08:02.920 --> 08:05.600
I guess word
really gets around in there.

08:05.680 --> 08:08.760
So Rollo wants your legs, but you're
cheating on Marta with those legs.

08:08.840 --> 08:11.160
Would you give me a break, please?
The legs are insanely jealous.

08:11.240 --> 08:15.160
Is that why you haven't seen Marta for the
past few days? This is about your love life.

08:15.280 --> 08:17.720
I can't believe it. Just forget it.
I came here to try to help...

08:17.800 --> 08:22.200
- Hey, I appreciate your time.
- Great. Great.

08:22.320 --> 08:24.200
You know what, Gob?

08:24.320 --> 08:28.040
Marta is a once-in-a-lifetime
woman. She's a treasure.

08:28.160 --> 08:30.240
And I don't think you're showing her
enough respect, okay?

08:30.360 --> 08:32.440
She doesn't respect my career.

08:35.039 --> 08:37.400
Okay.

08:37.480 --> 08:39.520
<i>He's having sex with a woman in his act?</i>

08:39.640 --> 08:42.039
I gotta tell Marta what's going on.

08:42.120 --> 08:45.280
First of all, she'll hate you for it.
It's called shoot the messenger.

08:45.360 --> 08:47.720
Secondly, it's not in your nature.
I mean, you're like Mr. Morals.

08:47.840 --> 08:49.960
- You can't even take a desk chair.
- Damn it.

08:50.080 --> 08:52.507
I
- I'm a saint, you know? I'm a living saint,

08:52.508 --> 08:54.520
and I get absolutely nothing out of it.

08:54.600 --> 08:57.240
Well, you get a false feeling
of superiority.

08:57.320 --> 08:59.800
I know. That is nice,
but this time, it's not enough.

08:59.880 --> 09:03.840
Why do I always have to be the one that
has to set the good example for everyone?

09:03.960 --> 09:07.600
- Hey, guys.
- Oh, that's why.

09:09.800 --> 09:12.000
- Hey, Mom.
- Hey, honey.

09:12.120 --> 09:15.200
Moo?

09:15.320 --> 09:17.960
Mmm. Moo, honey.

09:19.240 --> 09:21.760
You have to be some sort of
she hulk to get this.

09:21.880 --> 09:24.880
- You just gotta really dig.
- Well, it's not... enjoy...

09:24.960 --> 09:28.520
Oh, Maeby, great news.
I got my hands on some money.

09:28.640 --> 09:32.360
I can't say how or when...
or where my wedding ring is...

09:32.480 --> 09:36.720
but, my purse overfloweth
as do my high spirits...

09:36.800 --> 09:40.120
- so a-shopping we must go.
- Dad, we already went.

09:40.240 --> 09:43.680
That's why we're wearing all this leather.
I'm really into leather.

09:43.800 --> 09:47.520
- Tell Mom.
- Yes.

09:47.640 --> 09:51.010
- If you ever need to borrow
any money or anything...

09:51.011 --> 09:52.320
- No. Thank you, no.

09:52.400 --> 09:55.680
<i>So Tobias chose to pursue
a common interest with his daughter.</i>

09:55.800 --> 09:56.820
- May I help you?

09:56.821 --> 10:00.240
- I hope so. Um, I'm looking
for something that says...

10:00.320 --> 10:04.160
- "Dad likes leather. "
- Something that says, "leather daddy"?

10:04.280 --> 10:06.200
Oh, is there such a thing?

10:06.320 --> 10:08.680
<i>Later that day,
Michael got a surprise visit.</i>

10:08.800 --> 10:10.680
- Marta. What are you doing here?
- I was looking for Gob.

10:10.760 --> 10:13.920
- He said he was working here today.
- Oh, yes? Please.

10:14.040 --> 10:18.080
He said that, huh?
Said that he's working, huh? Wow. Here?

10:18.200 --> 10:21.640
What else did he say? Did he tell you
I gave him your message?

10:21.760 --> 10:24.360
- Not that I'm the messenger, you know?
- He told me.

10:24.480 --> 10:27.360
I don't know what you said to him,
but it really turned him around.

10:27.480 --> 10:31.320
- He said I was a treasure.
- She's a treasure.

10:31.400 --> 10:34.880
<i>And a once-in-a-lifetime
woman. - Mm-hmm.</i>

10:35.000 --> 10:39.160
Listen, Marta, Gob is...

10:41.560 --> 10:43.840
- a poet.
- Mm.

10:43.920 --> 10:46.920
He's touched. I'm gonna tell him
that you stopped by...

10:47.040 --> 10:50.040
- and, uh, you have a nice day.
- Thank you.

10:50.120 --> 10:53.320
You're such a good brother.
Always trying to help him.

10:53.440 --> 10:57.440
- He showed me the watch you gave him.
- The watch?

10:57.520 --> 10:59.720
I appreciate your time.

10:59.840 --> 11:03.320
<i>And so, for the first time,
Michael set a plan in motion...</i>

11:03.400 --> 11:05.440
<i>to take something
that didn't belong to him.</i>

11:05.560 --> 11:10.080
You know, I was thinking, I'd like to
help you guys out one more time.

11:10.160 --> 11:13.640
You know what you should do?
You should surprise Gob onstage.

11:13.760 --> 11:15.846
- I know that he's looking
for a new assistant.

11:15.847 --> 11:16.280
- Really?

11:16.400 --> 11:17.880
- Mm-hmm.
- Could you help me with that?

11:17.960 --> 11:22.240
- Yes.
- You really are a good guy, Michael.

11:22.320 --> 11:27.160
Well, you can't change who you are.

11:40.640 --> 11:43.120
<i>Michael went to
the popular magic parlor...</i>

11:43.200 --> 11:46.200
<i>the Gothic Castle, to ask a favor of Rollo.</i>

11:46.320 --> 11:51.520
I was wondering if, uh... if you would
give my brother a show?

11:51.600 --> 11:55.480
One more chance to get back in
with the Alliance. That's all I ask.

11:55.600 --> 11:57.760
<i>And-And you will get your legs back.</i>

11:57.880 --> 12:00.160
How?

12:00.240 --> 12:03.040
You're asking me to reveal my trick?

12:03.160 --> 12:05.440
<i>So Michael went to give
his brother the good news.</i>

12:05.520 --> 12:06.411
- Really, tomorrow night?

12:06.412 --> 12:08.800
- Yeah. You just gotta make sure
you do the sawing in half trick.

12:08.880 --> 12:10.920
- I don't even have a top half.
- Don't worry about that.

12:11.040 --> 12:12.806
I got someone I want you
to use. She's perfect.

12:12.807 --> 12:14.240
A great girl. You're doing me a favor.

12:14.360 --> 12:18.120
- Has she got big cans?
- I'll see ya there, Gob.

12:18.240 --> 12:20.320
- You're a good brother.
- You're a horrible brother, Michael.

12:20.440 --> 12:22.480
Pretty good, huh?

12:22.560 --> 12:25.120
You're gonna put Marta
onstage with the legs?

12:25.240 --> 12:28.080
It's gonna blow up.
Legs get upset. Marta gets upset.

12:28.160 --> 12:30.560
Marta leaves Gob,
and I don't get shot.

12:30.640 --> 12:32.680
You'll never be able to
pull the trigger on this.

12:32.800 --> 12:34.648
- You can't escape it,
Michael. You're the good guy.

12:34.649 --> 12:35.520
- Call me what you want.

12:35.600 --> 12:40.160
- An impotent man-boy?
- But it is done. The plan is in motion.

12:40.240 --> 12:45.200
- This just isn't you.
- It's me now. It's the me that can recline.

12:45.280 --> 12:48.480
- Did that hurt?
- No.

12:49.520 --> 12:52.040
This stuff's kind of hot, isn't it?

12:52.160 --> 12:55.160
- I hadn't noticed.
- Hey, gang.

12:55.240 --> 12:58.720
Mind if squeeze in here
for a moment? Oh!

12:58.840 --> 13:01.680
Look at us. Who'd wanna mess with
any of us, huh?

13:04.120 --> 13:06.640
- Excuse me.
- Yes. Oop.

13:08.960 --> 13:12.440
- Did you get a job or something?
- No. No, I didn't.

13:12.520 --> 13:16.640
Unless you consider
"World's Coolest Daddy" a job.

13:16.720 --> 13:20.240
If I...

13:20.320 --> 13:21.051
- Hey, Dad.

13:21.052 --> 13:24.640
- Hey, buddy. You're still
wearing that jacket, huh?

13:24.760 --> 13:27.160
- Yeah. I was just going for a new look.
- Yeah?

13:27.280 --> 13:29.360
Trying to introduce
some edge to the whole palette.

13:29.440 --> 13:32.000
- Hmm. Kind of liked you the way you were.
- You did?

13:32.120 --> 13:34.120
Yeah. I mean, we can't really change
who we are anyway, right?

13:34.240 --> 13:37.640
Wish you'd told me that before
I threw away my Windbreaker.

13:37.760 --> 13:38.965
- Oh, you bought a chair.

13:38.966 --> 13:41.760
- Uh, no, actually, I borrowed
it. Like we talked about.

13:41.880 --> 13:45.680
Well, I thought we decided
that was like stealing.

13:45.760 --> 13:47.880
Is that where we landed on that?

13:48.000 --> 13:49.640
<i>As Michael was becoming more selfish...</i>

13:49.760 --> 13:52.760
<i>his father was choosing
a more pious path.</i>

13:55.520 --> 13:59.600
<i>Which made Buster and Lucille's visit
go much differently than planned.</i>

13:59.680 --> 14:01.480
Why is there
a piece of shoe on your head?

14:01.600 --> 14:05.400
This is a... Well, it's a reminder that
the divine presence...

14:05.480 --> 14:07.280
is always above me.

14:07.360 --> 14:12.120
Well, more importantly,
Buster's been humping the widow Austero.

14:12.240 --> 14:14.040
- Mom.
- Is that true?

14:14.120 --> 14:16.680
No. We're taking it slow.

14:16.800 --> 14:20.000
He stays there sometimes
until 7:00, 8:00 at night.

14:20.120 --> 14:24.440
<i>Peanut brittle on his breath. Is she the one
who's going to take him to the dentist?</i>

14:24.560 --> 14:26.880
She already has.

14:34.400 --> 14:34.696
- What?

14:34.697 --> 14:37.280
- "May you live. May you be
well. I give you my blessing. "

14:37.360 --> 14:40.360
- Wow! Really?
- Are you out of your mind?

14:40.480 --> 14:42.491
- Just follow the heart
that God gave you, hmm?

14:42.492 --> 14:43.120
- No touching.

14:43.200 --> 14:47.200
No...

14:51.600 --> 14:54.280
Can you get me
some of that peanut brittle?

